Date: 0/0/1949
Source: Dictionary of Slang Addenda
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page:
Edition: 1166
Quote: <i>Shillings in the pound. eighteen</i> or, say, <i>twelve and six</i>, to indicate slight mental dullness or mild insanity; `He's only twelve and six in the pound': New Zealand: since ca. 1925. Niall Alexander, Oct. 22, 1939.
Notes:

